I"?<ol>
  <li>Cook the Rice and then set aside for 10 minutes to cool. Spread the rice over a large baking tray. Set aside to cool completely.</li>
  <li>Meanwhile, place the coconut in a non-stick frying pan over medium-low heat. Cook, stirring, for 1-2 minutes or until toasted.</li>
  <li>Combine the rice, coconut, mint, coriander, lemon grass, shallot, lime leaves, cucumber, celery and chilli, if desired, in a large serving bowl.</li>
  <li>Combine the lime juice and fish sauce in a jug. Add to the rice mixture. Toss to combine. Season with salt and pepper.</li>
</ol>
